</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 42-year-old Swede with a history of drug abuse and violence will be charged 
today with the 1986 murder of Swedish Prime Minister Olof Palme, Chief 
Prosecutor Anders Helin said in Stockholm. He said the case against Christer 
Pettersson was base on identification by several witnesses who were on the 
Stockholm street where Palme was fatally shot as he walked home from a movie 
with his wife. Pettersson, whose past crimes include the bayonet murder of a 
youth, has been in custody since last December while the prosecution has been 
preparing its case. 
</P>
