<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
France confirmed that it has received technical help from the United States in 
its nuclear weapons program but stressed that its nuclear deterrent remains 
totally independent. The Defense Ministry was reacting to an article in the 
U.S. magazine Foreign Policy claiming that Washington has secretly helped the 
French nuclear weapons program for the last 15 years in violation of U.S. law. 
U.S. officials, in an earlier statement confirming the exchange, said it did 
not violate any U.S. laws. French officials said there was no dependence of 
French nuclear forces on "foreign technologies" and no effect on "the 
independence of French decision-making." 
</P>
