<P>
The Berkeley Chamber of Commerce said that the City Council should be held 
responsible for this month's riot on Telegraph Avenue. In a blunt statement, 
the chamber blamed the council's "confrontational" attitude toward UC 
Berkeley's growth plans, which include construction of a dormitory in People's 
Park, for precipitating the violence. The outbreak, in which 28 stores were 
looted or damaged and 20 people were hurt, followed a demonstration to 
commemorate the 20-year-old struggle over People's Park, a piece of 
university-owned land near Telegraph Avenue. 
