<HEADLINE>
<P>
DERSHOWITZ ON PRENATAL RIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to "Drawing the Line on Prenatal Rights," by Alan Dershowitz, Op-Ed 
Page, May 14: 
</P>
<P>
With all due respect to Dershowitz, I am appalled by his position advocating 
state intervention in a woman's body once she has made the decision to bear a 
child over having an abortion. I also am a human rights activist, one perhaps 
who has been silent far too long! I am sure Dershowitz would have a different 
view on state intervention if the fetus in question was within his male body as 
opposed to the body of a woman. 
</P>
<P>
No government entity should have the right to dictate what one does with the 
inner sanctity of one's body -- suggest, educate, recommend, yes, but not 
intervene. Pregnant women are the first step in government intervention within 
the privacy of our bodies. Who will be the next target? Diabetics, cardiacs, 
hypertensives -- perhaps only allowed to order from a "special menu" in a 
restaurant or shop in a "special section" of the market -- by state 
intervention on the individual's behalf? Once unleashed, where will government 
intervention stop? Dershowitz has allowed himself to be manipulated by the 
right-to-life movement and, in so doing, has lost sight of what constitutes a 
democracy! 
</P>
<P>
SHEILA J. TENN 
</P>
<P>
Reseda 
</P>
</TEXT>
