<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Restrictions Put on Singer Co.: The firm has been barred from selling any of 
its assets or paying stock dividends pending a lawsuit about claims that a 
former subsidiary defrauded the government. The company, named as a 
co-defendant in a civil suit against its former Link Flight Simulation 
division, was also ordered not to incur any new debt or make any payments to 
investor Paul A. Bilzerian, the Florida financier who acquired the company last 
