<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rev. Jerry Falwell is cutting back on his television schedule. Falwell 
plans to discontinue his daily syndicated show "Pastor's Study" so that he can 
focus his energy on his religious teachings. Spokesman Mark DeMoss said Falwell 
is still deciding other activities to eliminate "that he doesn't deem critical 
or central to what's of utmost importance to him, and that's mainly Thomas Road 
Baptist Church and Liberty University," which are located in Lynchburg, Va. 
Falwell still will have his "Old Time Gospel Hour" on television, but "Pastor's 
Study" was taking too much time, he said, according to wire reports. The show, 
which ran for two years, featured interviews, musical performances and promoted 
the school andchurch. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
