<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
ANAHEIM OFFERS REWARD FOR ANTI-GRAFFITI HELP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Anaheim City Council is offering a $500 reward for information leading to 
the arrest and conviction of graffiti writers. 
</P>
<P>
Graffiti was responsible for a large number of the 1,000 nuisance complaints 
received by the city in the last year, said John Poole, code enforcement 
manager. 
</P>
<P>
Residents can report graffiti confidentially through a new bilingual hot line, 
(714) 776-1306. To report graffiti in progress, residents are asked to call 
(714) 999-1911. 
</P>
<P>
Graffiti-writing is a criminal offense punishable by a fine of up to $1,000 and 
6 months in jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
